This repository is an AI-agent-ready uv and pnpm workspace.

## Getting started

Install the toolchain specified in `.tool-versions`, then synchronize the
environment:

```sh
uv sync
pnpm install
```

## Repository guides

- `AGENTS.md` defines agent operating constraints.
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` defines repository-level architecture and invariants.
- `.agents/skills/` holds repository-scoped Agent Skills.
- `apps/` contains deployable applications and services.
- `packages/` contains reusable shared packages.
- uv and pnpm share the `.agents/skills`, `apps/*`, and `packages/*` workspace
  members. Each direct child package contains both `pyproject.toml` and
  `package.json`.

## Dependency policy

uv and pnpm resolve only registry packages that have been published for at
least three days. Commit `uv.lock` and `pnpm-lock.yaml` after reviewing changes.

The default PyPI and npm registries route through Takumi Guard's anonymous,
public package-registry proxies. They block known malicious public packages;
this repository stores no registry credential.

pnpm rejects dependency lifecycle build scripts unless their exact package and
version are explicitly approved in `allowBuilds` in `pnpm-workspace.yaml`.
Do not enable all dependency build scripts globally.
